# Security and API

## Explicit auth for endpoints
- Every HTTP and WebSocket endpoint must either use an auth guard (JWT/session) or be explicitly marked as public (e.g. health, login, webhook with HMAC).
- No unguarded endpoints by default. Document public routes in MODULE_DOC or API contracts.

## API versioning
- Public or partner-facing REST APIs must be versioned (e.g. `/api/v1/...`).
- Document versioning policy in API_EDGE_CONTRACTS or equivalent.

## Secrets and env
- No secrets in code or in MODULE_DOC.md.
- Env vars for secrets must be documented in a separate env.example or runbook; module docs may list only non-secret env var names.
